Script 1

Thank you for joining our beta testing stage. Please complete the following tests in the order they have been provided.
This script has actions that need to be performed by an admin, ensure that you have an admin with you to guide you in
completing this process.
If you encounter any errors throughout the process please inform the admin so we can continue to better our website.

To start, go to this link: https://cs-3240-my-study-buddy.herokuapp.com/

Test 1: Google login and on homepage
    1) Click on the button in the center of the screen labelled "Login With Google"
    2) Log in to the desired google account (should we expand this?)
    3) Assuming there was no previous log in, a screen to edit profile should be seen
    4) Make no edits and click the button labelled "Save Profile"
    5) The account info page with loggin in email should be seen
    6) Click on the words "Study Buddy" in the upper left hand corner
    7) The homepage with "Welcome to the Study Buddy App" should be seen

Test 2: User is able to add a course to their own course load
    1) If not logged in on homepage, follow Test 1
    2) Click on "Update Course Schedule" in the middle of the screen
    3) Click on the search bar with placeholder text of "Search for departments.."
    4) Type "cs"
    5) Click on the button labelled "CS"
    6) A screen with "Choose the class you would like to find a study buddy in" bolded should be seen on the screen
    7) Click on the search bar with placeholder text of "Search for courses in CS.."
    8) Type "3240"
    9) Click on the button labelled
        "CS3240: Advanced Software Development Techniques
        Instructor: Mark Sherriff
        (Section: 002)"
    10) A screen asking "Would you like to enroll in this course?" along with "Yes, enroll in this course." already
        preselected should be seen
    11) Click on the button labelled "Continue"
    12) The homepage with "CS 3240 - Section: 002" beneath "Update Course Schedule" should be seen

Test 3: User is able to make a post with default values for only the section they are enrolled in
    1) If not logged in on homepage, follow Test 1
    2) If "CS 3240 - Section: 002" is not seen on homepage, follow Test 2 to add course
    3) Click on the button labelled "CS 3240 - Section: 002", located beneath "Update Course Schedule" near the center of the screen
    4) The screen should show the following:
        "Find study buddy for:
         CS3240: Advanced Software Development Techniques
         Instructor: Mark Sherriff
         (Section: 002)"
    5) Click on the button labelled "Create a post!", located on the bottom right of the words from step 4
    6) The screen should show the following:
        "Make a study buddy post for:
         CS3240: Advanced Software Development Techniques
         Instructor: Mark Sherriff
         (Section: 002)"
    7) Do not edit anything on the screen and click the button labelled "Submit Post"
    8) The same screen from step 4 should be seen
    9) If not already seen on the screen, scroll down to see "Studybuddy posts for this course" along with the new post
       made in step 7
        "No topic was provided by the author of this post
        Author: sofia
        Time Frame: 2022-11-12 to 2022-11-19"
        **Where author is the name from login and Time Frame has today's date through one week later

Test 4: User is able to delete a post they made
    1) If not logged in on homepage, follow Test 1
    2) If "CS 3240 - Section: 002" is not seen on the homepage, follow Test 2 to add course
    3) If a post has not been made, follow Test 3
    4) If not already seen on the screen, scroll down to see "Studybuddy posts for this course"
    5) Look for the post made in Test 3 and click on the button labelled "Delete Post" beneath the post the made post
       from step 9 of Test 3
    6) Be on the same page and no longer see the post from step 9 of Test 3

Test 5: User is able to message another user to study together
    **Note: admin should check admin script (Lines 5-21) for actions to perform before testing with the user
    1) If not logged in on homepage, follow Test 1
    2) If "CS 3240 - Section: 002" is not seen on the homepage, follow Test 2 to add course
    3) Look for the following on the screen:
        "Find study buddy for:
         CS3240: Advanced Software Development Techniques
         Instructor: Mark Sherriff
         (Section: 002)"
        If not seen, follow steps 3 and 4 in Test 3
    5) If not already seen on the screen, reload and scroll down to see "Studybuddy posts for this course"
       along with the following post:
        "Beta Testing
        Author: adminX
        Time Frame: 11-21-2022 to 11-28-2022"
    6) Hover over the button labelled "View Description" and "this post is made for beta testing script 1" should be
       seen as a pop up with a grey background
    7) Click on the button labelled "Message Me!"
    8) The screen should show the following:
       "CS3240 - Beta Testing"
       Along with the user in this meeting room: adminX and the name from login, if there isn't a name, the logged in
       email should be seen
    ** Note: Admin should check admin script (Lines 24-31) for actions before proceeding
    9) Click on the message bar with "Your message" as a placeholder.
    10) Type "Hi! Let study together!".
    11) Click the button labelled "Send"
    ** Note: Admin should check admin script (Lines 33-38) for actions before proceeding
    12) The following message should be seen on the screen: "adminX : Yes!"

Test 6: User should be able to schedule a study session and see alerts when fields are not filled in properly
    1) If the following is not seen: "CS3240 - Beta Testing", follow Test 5
    2) If not already seen on the screen, scroll down to see and click on a button labelled "Schedule Study Session"
    3) The screen should show the following:
       "Schedule a study session for:
       CS3240 - Beta Testing"
    4) Click the button labelled "Schedule"
    5) An alert saying should be seen:
       "All fields must be filled in, the following fields are not filled:
       Date
       Start Time
       End Time"
    6) Click "Close" or "Ok" or any related button to close the alert (This is different depending on browser)
    7) Schedule a study session with the following fields:
       Date: 11/23/2022
       Start Time: 01:00 PM
       End Time: 02:00 PM
    8) Click on the button labelled "Schedule"
    9) The screen should show the following: "My Upcoming Study Sessions"
    10) Click on the dropdown labelled "Sent Study Session Requests"
    11) The following should be seen:
        "Study session for: Beta Testing
        Scheduled on: 11-23-2022
        Time Frame: 13:00 to 14:00"
        Along with a button labelled "Delete"
    ** Note: Admin should check admin script (Lines 41-50) for actions before proceeding
    12) Click "Study Sessions" in the navigation bar at the top of the screen then click on the dropdown
        labelled "Scheduled Study Sessions"
    13) The following should be seen:
        "Study session for: Beta Testing
        Scheduled on: 11-23-2022
        Time Frame: 13:00 to 14:00"
        Along with a button labelled "Delete"

Test 7: User is able to delete a study session
    1) If a scheduled study session has not been made, follow Test 6
    2) If the screen from step 13 of Test 6 is not already seen, follow step 12 in Test 6
    3) Click on the button labelled "Delete"
    4) If no other study sessions have been made, received, or declined the following message should be seen:
       "Note: You currently do not have any study sessions. To create a session you must have either message
       indicated interest in a user's study buddy post or have a post...."

       If other study sessions have been made, received, declined beyond the script here, the above message should not
       be seen

Test 8: User is able to see a message once they send a friend to a user in the system
    1) If not already logged in follow Test 1
    2) Click on "Friends" in the navigation bar at the top of the screen
    3) Click on the search bar with "example@email.com" as a placeholder
    4) Type "project@email.com"
    5) Click on the button labelled "Send a friend request"
    6) The following message should be seen:
        "You have successfully sent a friend request to project@email.com, they will show up on your friend list once
        they have accepted your request."
    7) Click on the dropdown "Sent Friend Requests", "project@email.com" should be seen
    **Note: Admin should check admin script (Lines 53-57) for actions before proceeding
    8) Refresh the page and click on the dropdown labelled "My Friends"
    9) "project@email.com" along with a button labelled "Unfriend" should be seen

Test 9: User is able to see message when they send a friend request to someone they are already friends with
    1) If not already logged in follow Test 1
    2) If not already friends with "project@email.com", follow Test 8
    3) Follow steps 2-5 from Test 8
    4) The following message should be seen:
        "You are already friends with user with email project@email.com. You can see them in the 'My Friends' dropdown"

Test 10: User is able to change their account profile
    1) If not already logged in, follow Test 1
    2) Click on "My Account" in the navigation bar at the top of the page
    3) On the right side of the screen, click on the button labelled "Edit Profile"
    4) Click on the text box with "About Me:" to the left of it
    5) Type "Nice to meet everyone!"
    6) If "Save Profile" is not already seen on the screen, scroll down and click on the button labelled "Save Profile"
    7) "Nice to meet everyone!" should be seen on the screen in blue text above "Username"

Test 11: User is able to log and return to the login page
    1) If not already logged in, follow Test 1
    2) Click on "Logout adminX" where 'adminX' is the name of the logged in account that is located in the navigation
       bar at the top of the screen
    3) "Login with Google" should be seen on the screen.

You have finished the beta testing scripts. Please inform admin about any other feedback you have about the UX or
functionality of our website. Thank you so much for participating!